org.conqat.engine.commons.findings

Class DetachedFinding

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.conqat.engine.commons.findings.DetachedFinding
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, IDeepCloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    IndexFinding

    public class DetachedFinding
extends java.lang.Object
implements IDeepCloneable, java.io.Serializable
    This class describes orphaned finding that is attached to a node or a findings report. This is useful if e.g. findings have been filtered but certain operations should still be carried out on the findings.

      • getStatementPath

        public java.util.List<StatementPathElement> getStatementPath()
        Returns the statement path if there is one attached to this finding. A statementPath is a path through the program that leads to this finding. The path may not be a simple chain, but could be a DAG. Each entry in the list refers to the indices of its predecessor statements. Contract for the setup of this structure:
        • An element might have more than one predecessor.
        • Multiple elements can have the same predecessor.
        • There are no cycles in the path.
